      "source": {
        "issue": {
          "active_lock_reason": null,
          "assignee": null,
          "assignees": [],
          "author_association": "MEMBER",
          "body": "Filed from the pd-book-tools deep code/security review.\n\nReport: `docs/research/2026-05-22-deep-code-security-review.md`\nFinding: #21\n\nMoved from mistakenly filed meta issue: ConcaveTrillion/ocr-container-meta#314\n\nEvidence:\n\n- `pd_book_tools/image_processing/cv2_processing/edge_finding.py:48`\n- `pd_book_tools/image_processing/cupy_processing/edge_finding.py:55`\n\nCPU uses `np.convolve(..., mode=\"same\")`, while GPU uses `convolve1d(..., mode=\"nearest\")`.\n\nImpact:\n\n- Content touching image borders can produce different edge boxes across backends.\n\nRemediation:\n\n- Choose one boundary contract and implement it consistently.\n- Add parity tests with content at all image edges.\n\n---\nThis issue was filed from a read-only review. Confirm behavior with a focused failing test before implementation where practical.",
          "closed_at": "2026-05-25T02:48:47Z",
          "comments": 1,
          "comments_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/pdomain/pdomain-book-tools/issues/185/comments",
          "created_at": "2026-05-22T16:02:39Z",
